Review Text: The food is delicious and very tasty. The portions are small so I always end up wanting to have seconds. The four times that I've been there, the service was quick but not very warm. But it's a small, family business that is always packed and the food is excellent.

Name: Eethuis Sie-Joe

Name: Eethuis Sie-Joe
Review Text: To Indonesians that longing for home cooked food, you should go to this place! Nasi goreng, lontong kuah, bakmi kuah are as good as in Indonesia. You can fulfill your sambal craving since they have our lovely Sambal Belibis right on your table!

Name: Eethuis Sie-Joe
Review Text: It's not only about the taste of its cuisine, its also about the ambience (I'm also speaking about the language spoken). Indonesian people, diaspores, or tourists will find their second home here. For Indonesian, feels like they are going nowhere but home.

Name: Eethuis Sie-Joe
Review Text: A nice and cozy Indonesian resturant in the city centre. The food is very good and reasonably priced. We loved the food. The fried rice noodles were amazing.

Name: Eethuis Sie-Joe

Name: Eethuis Sie-Joe
